What’s for dinner tonight? Molcajete 🔥 
In the state of Sonora Molcajete’s is one of the regions signature dishes. It started with locals putting cold marinated seafoods into the massive volcanic rock mortars. The shareable dish became so popular that the locals experimented with hot dishes. Molcajete are made with volcano rocks that store heat nicely keeping the dishes warm. Here at Barrio Queen we created a combination of seafood, meats, cheeses put together in a beautiful presentation. Molcajetes are popular all over Mexico and it’s an honor to bring them into the United States. :
